---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import EditorialNote from "../components/EditorialNote.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Corrections Policy - WattCostGuide"
  description="How to report a WattCostGuide error and how calculator, source, and editorial corrections are reviewed and documented."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">Accuracy and transparency</p>
    <h1>Corrections Policy</h1>
    <p>How WattCostGuide reviews reported errors and updates calculations, sources, and explanatory content.</p>
  </section>

  <EditorialNote
    updated="June 21, 2026"
    note="Correction requests are reviewed against the calculation formula and the most relevant reliable source available."
  />

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>How to report an issue</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href="mailto:hello@wattcostguide.com">hello@wattcostguide.com</a> with the page URL, the value or
      statement that appears incorrect, the expected correction, and a supporting source when available. For a
      calculator issue, include the watts, hours, electricity rate, and result you received.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>How reports are reviewed</h2>
    <p>
      We reproduce calculation reports using the displayed formula, then compare factual reports with appliance
      labels, manuals, manufacturer specifications, government energy resources, or other authoritative material.
      A single model may not justify changing a range intended to cover a broader appliance category.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Minor and material corrections</h2>
    <p>
      Spelling, formatting, and broken-link repairs may be made without a correction notice when they do not change
      meaning. A material correction changes a calculation, default assumption, wattage range, source attribution,
      or conclusion that could affect a reader's estimate.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>How updates are documented</h2>
    <p>
      When a calculator receives a substantive review, its independent last-reviewed date is updated. Material
      corrections that require additional context will be noted on the affected page or documented here. There are
      currently no published material correction notices.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Response limits</h2>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide can review site content but cannot resolve utility account disputes, verify household wiring,
      diagnose appliances, or provide individualized engineering or financial advice.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
